# Normalize all text files to LF in the repository to prevent CRLF<->LF churn on
# Windows. This is important because the built dist/ output is committed: without
# this, every `npm run build` on a Windows checkout (core.autocrlf=true) marks
# ~35 dist files modified with pure line-ending flips. `text=auto` lets git
# detect binary files and leave them untouched.
* text=auto eol=lf
